version, prices were in pound and so on.Here is the answer from
yahoo! uk after i tried to convince them to change their mind:

-------------- answer yahoo ---------------------------

Thank you for your mail. We have reviewed the site once more but the
content of http://uk-site.and http://us-site Xppears to be identical
despite the difference in layout. As the content is not unique our
decision to not add http://uk-site to the directory remains
unchanged. ... and so on ...

-------------------------------------------------------

but you may try it, perhaps you have more luck and get another
editor withis more gracious.

>> We plan in the future to create a German site with the same
content in German. Would this be seen as a significantly different
site so as not to be thrown out of a search engine or directory
because the USA site is already listed? <<

Searchengines will take the German site without problems. And the
same forthe catalogs. In the above case it was no problem to get the
site intoYahoo! DE. And that's very reasonable, otherwise german
customers would not be able to find/use the site/content.

